Package game.dinosaurs

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Huntable
    An interface of which all hunting Actors implement.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Allosaur
    A carnivorous dinosaur.
    AttackAction
    Special Action for attacking other Actors.
    Brachiosaur
    A herbivorous Dinosaur.
    DieAction
    Called when an Actor is dead, responsible for replacing the Actor with its Corpse.
    Dinosaur
    A dinosaur class that contains all the dinosaur logic.
    DrinkAction
    The action of Dinosaurs drinking water from a water body.
    EatFromSearchableGroundAction
    Action representing Dinosaurs eating food inside Grounds.
    EatItemOnGroundAction
    For dinosaurs to feed on Items on the Ground.
    FeedAction
    Feeds an Actor an Item, healing effect varies across dinosaur species.
    FollowBehaviour
    A class that figures out a MoveAction that will move the actor one step closer to a target Actor.
    HungryBehaviour
    A class that makes dinosaurs move to a food source and eat it.
    LayEggAction
    Handles Dinosaurs' lay egg action/logic.
    MateAction
    Handles Dinosaur mating action/logic.
    MatingBehaviour
    A class that figures out the actions of two compatible dinosaurs when they are available to mate.
    PreyingBehaviour
    A class for carnivorous dinosaurs to hunt down preys.
    Pterodactyl
    A tiny flying dinosaur.
    RechargeSkillBehaviour
    Represents the behaviour where the Dinosaur goes to a predefined Ground, to recharge its skills (represented by capabilities).
    Stegosaur
    A herbivorous dinosaur.
    ThirstyBehaviour
    A class for dinosaurs to find water source and quench their thirst.
    WanderBehaviour
    Allows Actors to wander around randomly without a clear direction.
